General Enquiry from the Website

NameRachael Yeardley Emailrakki89@aol.com=
 Phone07960021306 MessageHello, I'm looking for an independent automotive =
engineer to inspect my vehicle and prepare a report for a County Court =
claim under the Consumer Rights Act 2015. The vehicle is a 2019 Nissan =
Navara, 26,000 miles, purchased from a dealer on 26 May 2026. The vehicle =
felt unstable immediately after purchase and was booked into to a mechanic.=
 The garage found both rear suspension springs broken and rusted, two tyres=
 below the legal tread limit and a third tyre with significant outer edge =
wear consistent with a tracking or alignment issue. The dealer disputes =
that these defects were present when the vehicle was sold and relies on the=
 MOT, pre-delivery inspection and handover video. I'm not looking for =
another inspection simply confirming the faults. I'm looking for an =
independent opinion on: Whether the defects are more likely than not to =
have been present, or developing, at the time of sale. Whether the =
condition of the broken rear springs (including the fracture surfaces and =
any corrosion present) indicates a recent failure or one that had existed =
before I purchased the vehicle. Whether the tyre wear identified could =
realistically have developed during approximately 700 miles of normal =
driving. Whether the combination of defects is consistent with a vehicle =
that was of satisfactory quality when supplied. Whether, in your opinion, =
these defects would ordinarily have been identified during a competent MOT =
or pre-delivery inspection. Whether there is anything about the defects =
that indicates they arose after the sale, or whether the evidence is more =
consistent with them having existed beforehand. Whether the vehicle has =
further damage i am not aware of. Could you let me know: Whether this is =
something you can assist with. Whether you've prepared reports for court =
before. The likely cost of an inspection and report. How soon you would be =
able to inspect the vehicle. The vehicle is parked at my home address and =
with both suspension coils broken, is not currently driveable Many thanks, =
Rachael Yeardley

Submitted via the Collision Engineers website contact =
form.
